The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of matrices to obtain lower bounds suggests that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant. The problem of determining if two strings differ in a certain number of bits is related to the study of combinatorial objects such as codes and graphs, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of lower bounds on communication complexity often involves analyzing the structure of the problem, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the use of quantum protocols suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the study of quantum computing and quantum information theory (cs.LG).
